			<div class="col-md-12">
			<h1>Unarmed Resources</h1>

			<p>My martial arts instructor Wu Wei of Beijing told me, “Before you can seek to use a weapon, you must seek to first master your body….to properly use any weapon you will need a trained body.”  The meaning of what he expressed to me rang true to the core.  No matter how wonderful, fancy or amazing a weapon may be it is simply a tool; if it’s welder is inept the weapon will be useless.  This speaks to the mindset of people being afraid of using a weapon, gun, knife, etc. as it may be used against them.  That perspective is a defeatist ideal, and has no place for those who seek to empower themselves to protect life and liberty.  The perspective should be I will learn to use my body, mind and weapon properly so that no one can infringe on me.  These links below are places that will help you in the mindset and mastery needed to properly defend oneself. </p>
				
			</div>
		</div>

